ObjectLike
public class JsMouseEvent
extends DOM2Event.MouseEvent.Prototype

An opaque class representing JavaScript client-side objects of the global JsClient.MouseEvent class.

The class represents the events of types "click", "mousedown", "mousemove", "mouseout", "mouseover", and "mouseup". Note that in addition to the property members defined in this class, it also inherits the properties of JsUIEvent and JsEvent.

Author:
J.J.Liu (Jianjun Liu) at http://www.jscripter.org
JavaScript:
Opaque types can be resolved but no class objects for them can be generated into the target codes. Re-compilers must exit with error on the operations of accessing that kind of class objects. The checkcast operation to the class literal of this interface must be ignored and instanceof to it always true.

button

public static final Value.Integer.Member button

An opaque static field defining a member that is named by the field name without a qualifying member and to access the property of the name on an object.

The property, identified by this member, of a JsMouseEvent object refers to a read-only integer value which tells which mouse button changed state during a "mousedown", "mouseup", or "click" event. A value of 0 indicates the left button, a value of 2 indicates the right button, and a value of 1 indicates the middle mouse button. Note that this property is defined when a button changes state; it is not used to report whether a button is held down during a "mousemove" event. Also, this property is not a bitmap, that is, it cannot tell you if more than one button is held down.

Since:
1.0
JavaScript:
Re-compilers must resolve the member of this static field to the identifier of the field name.

clientX

public static final Value.Integer.Member clientX

An opaque static field defining a member that is named by the field name without a qualifying member and to access the property of the name on an object.

The property, identified by this member, of a JsMouseEvent object refers to a read-only integer value representing the X-coordinate of the mouse pointer relative to the "client area", or browser window. Note that this value does not take document scrolling into account; if an event occurs at the very top of the window, the value is 0 regardless of how far down the document has been scrolled.

Since:
1.0

relatedTarget

public static final JsElement.Member relatedTarget

An opaque static field defining a member that is named by the field name without a qualifying member and to access the property of the name on an object.

The property, identified by this member, of a JsMouseEvent object is a read-only reference to a JsElement node that is related to the JsEvent.target node of the event. For "mouseover" events, it is the JsElement object that the mouse left when it moved over the target. For "mouseout" events, it is the JsElement object that the mouse entered when leaving the target.

Since:
1.0

Initializes the properties of a newly created JsMouseEvent object.

This method initializes the various properties of the JsMouseEvent object and may be called only before it is passed to JsElement.dispatchEvent(JsEvent).

Parameters:
eventType - The type of event.
canBubble - Specifies whether the event will bubble.
cancelable - Specifies whether the event can be canceled with JsEvent.preventDefault().
view - The JsWindow object in which the event occurred.
detail - The JsUIEvent.detail property for the event.
screenX - Specifies the initial value of the screenX property of this JsMouseEvent object.
screenY - Specifies the initial value of the screenY property of this JsMouseEvent object.
clientX - Specifies the initial value of the clientX property of this JsMouseEvent object.
clientY - Specifies the initial value of the clientY property of this JsMouseEvent object.
ctrlKey - Specifies the initial value of the ctrlKey property of this JsMouseEvent object.
altKey - Specifies the initial value of the altKey property of this JsMouseEvent object.
shiftKey - Specifies the initial value of the shiftKey property of this JsMouseEvent object.
metaKey - Specifies the initial value of the metaKey property of this JsMouseEvent object.
button - Specifies the initial value of the button property of this JsMouseEvent object.
relatedTarget - Specifies the initial value of the relatedTarget property of this JsMouseEvent object.
Since:
